(CLICK)

67
00:03:16.263 --> 00:03:17.796
What the hell...

68
00:03:33.980 --> 00:03:34.980
Oh!

69
00:03:37.017 --> 00:03:38.828
Thank God! Where
the hell have you been?

70
00:03:38.852 --> 00:03:41.292
Do you have any idea
what's been going on?

71
00:03:44.959 --> 00:03:46.625
I really don't get lacrosse.

72
00:03:47.928 --> 00:03:49.110
It was you...

73
00:03:49.179 --> 00:03:52.130
When I was in high school.
we played basketball.

74
00:03:52.198 --> 00:03:54.749
There's a real sport.

75
00:03:54.818 --> 00:03:57.869
Still. I read somewhere that lacrosse
comes from Native American tribes

76
00:03:57.938 --> 00:03:59.921
and that they played
it to resolve conflict.

77
00:04:01.658 --> 00:04:04.326
Do I have that right? Well...

78
00:04:06.346 --> 00:04:08.913
I have a little conflict of
my own to resolve. Scott.

79
00:04:12.686 --> 00:04:14.726
But I need your help to do it.

80
00:04:15.104 --> 00:04:17.973
I'm not helping you kill people.

81
00:04:18.042 --> 00:04:20.442
Well. I don't want
to kill all of them.

82
00:04:22.045 --> 00:04:24.346
Just the responsible ones.

83
00:04:24.414 --> 00:04:26.881
And that doesn't
have to include...

84
00:04:29.486 --> 00:04:30.552
Allison.

85
00:04:35.125 --> 00:04:37.709
You're on his side?

86
00:04:37.778 --> 00:04:41.378
Are you forgetting the part
where he killed your sister?

87
00:04:42.048 --> 00:04:43.431
It was a mistake.

88
00:04:45.736 --> 00:04:47.168
What?

89
00:04:47.237 --> 00:04:49.187
It happens. PETER: Scott...

90
00:04:51.358 --> 00:04:54.660
I think you're getting the
wrong impression of us.

91
00:04:54.728 --> 00:04:57.896
We really just want to help
you reach your full potential.

92
00:04:57.965 --> 00:04:59.881
By killing my friends.

93
00:04:59.950 --> 00:05:02.310
Sometimes the
people closest to you...

94
00:05:03.586 --> 00:05:06.238
can be the ones holding
you back the most.

95
00:05:06.306 --> 00:05:10.208
If they're holding me back from
becoming a psychotic nut job like you...

96
00:05:12.879 --> 00:05:14.279
I'm okay with that.

97
00:05:21.105 --> 00:05:22.354
Maybe...

98
00:05:22.423 --> 00:05:24.743
You could try and see things...

99
00:05:27.644 --> 00:05:29.544
From my perspective.

100
00:05:31.165 --> 00:05:32.880
(GRUNTING)

101
00:05:35.719 --> 00:05:37.152
(GROANING)

102
00:05:39.189 --> 00:05:40.872
(GRUNTING)

103
00:05:45.628 --> 00:05:47.378
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

104
00:05:53.203 --> 00:05:54.283
Aah!

105
00:06:04.531 --> 00:06:05.531
(GROWLS)

106
00:06:06.333 --> 00:06:07.415
Aah!

107
00:06:12.772 --> 00:06:14.456
(SCREAMING)

108
00:06:23.083 --> 00:06:24.115
(GROWLING)

109
00:06:24.184 --> 00:06:25.500
(SCREAMING)

110
00:06:37.798 --> 00:06:38.798
Peter?

111
00:06:58.918 --> 00:07:00.118
(GASPS)

112
00:07:05.225 --> 00:07:07.625
Dude. we have a huge problem.

113
00:07:07.661 --> 00:07:11.930
Trust me... I know.

114
00:07:11.998 --> 00:07:14.298
<i>(HELP ME CLOSE MY EYES</i> PLAYING)

115
00:07:21.925 --> 00:07:25.894
<i>♪ Help me close my eyes</i>

116
00:07:25.963 --> 00:07:30.765
<i>♪ I don't want to see
what this day was like</i>

117
00:07:30.834 --> 00:07:33.434
<i>♪ Help me close my eyes</i>

118
00:07:33.520 --> 00:07:37.322
<i>♪ I want to sleep
without dreaming</i>

119
00:07:37.390 --> 00:07:40.592
<i>♪ 'Cause I need them to be true</i>

120
00:07:40.661 --> 00:07:45.447
<i>♪ I want to hide but
trees are falling down</i>

121
00:07:45.515 --> 00:07:50.084
<i>♪ I want to hide but
mountains are melting</i>

122
00:07:50.153 --> 00:07:55.323
<i>♪ I want to hide but
trees are falling down</i>

123
00:07:55.392 --> 00:07:59.594
<i>♪ To hide Help me close my eyes</i>

124
00:07:59.662 --> 00:08:04.115
<i>♪ I want to hide Help
me close my eyes ♪</i>

125
00:08:23.086 --> 00:08:24.953
(GARAGE DOOR CLATTERS)

126
00:08:31.728 --> 00:08:34.129
CHRIS: It hasn't been an
issue since we lived here.

127
00:08:34.197 --> 00:08:36.642
All I'm saying is that firing
those things so close by

128
00:08:36.666 --> 00:08:38.733
is bound to draw some attention.

129
00:08:38.802 --> 00:08:41.586
These things have saved
my life more than once.

130
00:08:41.654 --> 00:08:44.951
and I know how to be
inconspicuous when I need to.

131
00:08:44.975 --> 00:08:48.371
This coming from a man whose
preferred weapon is a crossbow.

132
00:08:48.395 --> 00:08:51.555
You know these extra skills are something
you could be teaching your daughter.

133
00:08:52.849 --> 00:08:54.448
Not yet.

134
00:08:56.619 --> 00:08:57.952
Ever?

135
00:08:58.021 --> 00:08:59.738
CHRIS: Not yet.

136
00:09:02.342 --> 00:09:03.342
You coming?

137
00:09:06.229 --> 00:09:08.562
Yeah. Coming.

138
00:09:51.858 --> 00:09:53.407
(FAST ROCK MUSIC)

139
00:09:56.730 --> 00:09:58.379
(TIRES SCREECHING)

140
00:09:59.633 --> 00:10:00.814
(BEEPING)

141
00:10:10.376 --> 00:10:11.760
(BEEPING)

142
00:10:14.097 --> 00:10:15.297
(HORN HONKS)

143
00:10:35.434 --> 00:10:36.594
Car trouble?

144
00:10:38.004 --> 00:10:39.737
Allison. when you
said you needed

145
00:10:39.806 --> 00:10:42.140
to stop for an errand
before we went shopping.

146
00:10:42.209 --> 00:10:45.910
a five-mile hike in the woods
was not what I was expecting.

147
00:10:45.979 --> 00:10:49.347
Before I forget. I wanted to
ask if you're okay with something.

148
00:10:49.415 --> 00:10:51.783
Jackson asked me
to the winter formal.

149
00:10:53.019 --> 00:10:55.119
Did he? Yeah.

150
00:10:55.188 --> 00:10:58.548
Just as friends. But I just wanted
to make sure you're okay with it first.

151
00:10:59.693 --> 00:11:03.127
Sure. As long
as it's just friends.

152
00:11:03.196 --> 00:11:05.363
Well. yeah. I mean... (CHUCKLES)

153
00:11:05.431 --> 00:11:07.977
It's not like I would take him to the
coach's office during lacrosse practice

154
00:11:08.001 --> 00:11:10.161
to make out with
him or anything.

155
00:11:10.837 --> 00:11:11.936
Uh...

156
00:11:12.906 --> 00:11:14.238
About that...

157
00:11:15.492 --> 00:11:17.691
It's okay. I'm just
gonna call a tow truck.

158
00:11:17.761 --> 00:11:19.927
Oh. I know a few
things about cars.

159
00:11:19.996 --> 00:11:22.116
Might be something simple.

160
00:11:22.598 --> 00:11:24.215
I don't know.

161
00:11:24.283 --> 00:11:26.228
It's a pretty expensive car and
they pull all this warranty crap

162
00:11:26.252 --> 00:11:27.563
if you do your
own repairs. right?

163
00:11:27.587 --> 00:11:29.053
Well...

164
00:11:29.122 --> 00:11:31.082
I won't tell if you won't.

165
00:11:31.691 --> 00:11:33.558
It's Jackson. right?

166
00:11:33.627 --> 00:11:36.067
Come here. I'll show
you what to look for.

167
00:11:45.288 --> 00:11:47.672
Oh. sorry. What?

168
00:11:48.224 --> 00:11:49.607
Your neck.

169
00:11:49.675 --> 00:11:52.243
You hurt yourself?

170
00:11:52.312 --> 00:11:56.714
Um. no. I mean. it's
just... Just a scratch.

171
00:11:56.783 --> 00:11:58.878
Well. it looks like
more than a scratch.

172
00:11:58.902 --> 00:12:01.102
Kind of looks like claw marks.

173
00:12:05.075 --> 00:12:07.575
You all right?

174
00:12:07.643 --> 00:12:09.843
Yeah. look. I'm just gonna
call for a tow truck. okay?

175
00:12:12.465 --> 00:12:16.065
Is there any reason you're so reluctant
to tell me what it was that did that?

176
00:12:17.053 --> 00:12:18.769
(TIRES SCREECHING)

177
00:12:18.838 --> 00:12:20.472
(LOUD ROCK MUSIC)

178
00:12:22.709 --> 00:12:24.676
Yo. What's up?

179
00:12:24.744 --> 00:12:25.759
Is everything okay?

180
00:12:25.828 --> 00:12:28.195
Hey. Scott.

181
00:12:28.264 --> 00:12:30.993
Your friend here was having car
trouble. We're just taking a look.

182
00:12:31.017 --> 00:12:33.061
Wow. There's a shop
right down the street.

183
00:12:33.085 --> 00:12:34.296
I'm sure they have a tow truck.

184
00:12:34.320 --> 00:12:35.560
Yeah. You want a ride?

185
00:12:39.059 --> 00:12:40.841
Hey. come on. Jackson.

186
00:12:40.910 --> 00:12:43.790
You're way too pretty to
be out here all by yourself.

187
00:12:53.856 --> 00:12:55.490
Hey. boys.

188
00:13:00.246 --> 00:13:01.846
(ENGINE STARTS)

189
00:13:01.915 --> 00:13:03.593
Told you I knew a
few things about cars.

190
00:13:03.617 --> 00:13:05.149
(ENGINE IDLING)

191
00:13:10.072 --> 00:13:11.372
(SECOND ENGINE STARTS)

192
00:13:17.313 --> 00:13:18.812
What. are you following me now?

193
00:13:18.882 --> 00:13:20.259
Yes. you stupid freaking idiot.

194
00:13:20.283 --> 00:13:22.328
You almost gave away
everything right there!

195
00:13:22.352 --> 00:13:23.935
What are you talking about?

196
00:13:24.004 --> 00:13:26.287
He thinks you're
the second Beta.

197
00:13:26.355 --> 00:13:27.355
What?

198
00:13:27.424 --> 00:13:28.639
He thinks you're me!

199
00:13:28.708 --> 00:13:29.785
(GRUNTS)

200
00:13:29.809 --> 00:13:31.309
Dude. my jeep.

201
00:13:31.377 --> 00:13:34.195
I can hear your heart beating
from a mile away. literally!

202
00:13:34.264 --> 00:13:35.908
Now he thinks that
there's something wrong.

203
00:13:35.932 --> 00:13:39.345
and now I have to keep an eye
on you so he doesn't kill you. too!

204
00:13:39.369 --> 00:13:40.809
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
okay. okay. okay.

205
00:13:40.870 --> 00:13:42.381
How about we just step
away from Stiles' jeep?

206
00:13:42.405 --> 00:13:44.449
You know what. this is your
problem. not mine. okay?

207
00:13:44.473 --> 00:13:45.968
I didn't say anything.
which means you're the one

208
00:13:45.992 --> 00:13:47.742
that's gonna get
me killed. okay?

209
00:13:47.811 --> 00:13:49.955
This is your fault. Can
we stop hitting my jeep?

210
00:13:49.979 --> 00:13:51.929
Yo. all right. yo.
guys. stop. All right?

211
00:13:54.600 --> 00:13:56.078
When they come after you.

212
00:13:56.102 --> 00:13:58.064
I won't be able to protect you.

213
00:13:58.088 --> 00:13:59.437
I can't protect anyone.

214
00:14:00.824 --> 00:14:02.464
Why are you looking at me?

215
00:14:06.145 --> 00:14:08.213
You know what?
Now you have to do it.

216
00:14:08.281 --> 00:14:11.599
Get me what I want. and I
will be fine protecting myself.

217
00:14:11.667 --> 00:14:13.101
No. you won't!

218
00:14:13.169 --> 00:14:16.620
Just trust me. all it does
is make things worse.

219
00:14:16.689 --> 00:14:18.523
Oh. yeah. really?

220
00:14:18.592 --> 00:14:21.304
You know. you can hear anything you
want and run faster than humanly possible.

221
00:14:21.328 --> 00:14:23.077
Sounds like a real
hardship. McCall.

222
00:14:23.146 --> 00:14:25.680
Yeah. I can run really fast now.

223
00:14:25.749 --> 00:14:29.149
except half the time. I'm running
away from people trying to kill me!

224
00:14:30.487 --> 00:14:32.582
And I can hear things like...

225
00:14:32.606 --> 00:14:35.084
Like my girlfriend telling people
that she doesn't trust me anymore

226
00:14:35.108 --> 00:14:36.352
right before
breaking up with me.

227
00:14:36.376 --> 00:14:37.708
I'm not lying to you!

228
00:14:39.445 --> 00:14:41.345
It ruins your life.

229
00:14:42.715 --> 00:14:44.498
It ruined your life.

230
00:14:44.567 --> 00:14:46.066
You had all the
power in the world.

231
00:14:46.136 --> 00:14:48.068
and you didn't know
what to do with it.

232
00:14:48.138 --> 00:14:49.837
You know what
it's actually like?

233
00:14:49.905 --> 00:14:52.373
It's like you turned 16 and
someone bought you a Porsche

234
00:14:52.442 --> 00:14:55.002
when they should have started
you out with a nice little Honda.

235
00:14:55.728 --> 00:14:56.761
Me?

236
00:14:58.298 --> 00:14:59.897
I drive a Porsche.

237
00:15:05.888 --> 00:15:07.171
(ENGINE REVS)

238
00:15:11.343 --> 00:15:12.777
What does that do?

239
00:15:14.514 --> 00:15:16.213
We're about to find out.

240
00:15:32.832 --> 00:15:34.698
What the hell was that?

241
00:15:36.735 --> 00:15:38.069
I don't know.

242
00:15:44.127 --> 00:15:47.194
Well. that was fun!

243
00:15:47.263 --> 00:15:48.773
Any more lethal weapons
you wanna try out?

244
00:15:48.797 --> 00:15:50.197
(TWIG SNAPS)

245
00:15:54.553 --> 00:15:55.553
(SNAPS)

246
00:16:00.109 --> 00:16:01.349
(SNAP)

247
00:16:04.547 --> 00:16:06.213
Hold this.

248
00:16:06.282 --> 00:16:09.584
What? Why? Because I
thought I heard something.

249
00:16:09.652 --> 00:16:11.452
So what if you heard something?

250
00:16:11.521 --> 00:16:14.455
So. I want to find out
what that something is.

251
00:16:14.524 --> 00:16:16.791
Don't worry. It's
probably nothing.

252
00:16:16.860 --> 00:16:20.194
Well. what if that nothing is something
and that something is something dangerous?

253
00:16:20.263 --> 00:16:21.863
Shoot it.

254
00:16:23.783 --> 00:16:24.783
(WHIMPERS)

255
00:16:25.552 --> 00:16:27.284
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

256
00:16:55.598 --> 00:16:56.692
(CLICKS)

257
00:16:56.716 --> 00:16:58.165
(ELECTRIC PULSING)

258
00:16:58.234 --> 00:17:00.184
Scott? (GROANING)

259
00:17:00.252 --> 00:17:01.252
Scott!

260
00:17:02.155 --> 00:17:03.182
Trigger finger!

261
00:17:03.206 --> 00:17:04.722
Oh! Oh. God. oh. God.

262
00:17:04.791 --> 00:17:06.602
I'm so. so. so. so sorry.

263
00:17:06.626 --> 00:17:09.093
Oh. no. it's my
fault. Totally my fault.

264
00:17:09.162 --> 00:17:10.411
Are you okay?

265
00:17:10.479 --> 00:17:12.096
Yeah. I'm fine.

266
00:17:12.164 --> 00:17:13.642
I didn't know it was you. If I
would have known it was you. I...

267
00:17:13.666 --> 00:17:14.943
Still would have
pulled the trigger?

268
00:17:14.967 --> 00:17:18.335
No! Of course not.
Seriously. I'm so sorry.

269
00:17:18.404 --> 00:17:19.644
(GRUNTS)

270
00:17:21.024 --> 00:17:22.440
Are you sure you're okay?

271
00:17:23.742 --> 00:17:28.028
Yeah. I think so.

272
00:17:28.097 --> 00:17:30.781
What were you doing here
anyway? Were you following us?

273
00:17:30.850 --> 00:17:33.584
No. Not at all.

274
00:17:33.653 --> 00:17:37.033
Um. your dad told me that
you run this trail sometimes.

275
00:17:37.057 --> 00:17:39.168
and I was hoping
to catch you alone.

276
00:17:39.192 --> 00:17:40.958
By following me?

277
00:17:41.026 --> 00:17:42.793
Well. yeah.

278
00:17:43.879 --> 00:17:44.879
What for?

279
00:17:45.681 --> 00:17:47.014
Well...

280
00:17:47.817 --> 00:17:49.767
I found this at school.

281
00:17:53.656 --> 00:17:54.856
(GASPS)

282
00:17:55.508 --> 00:17:56.941
Thank God!

283
00:17:58.044 --> 00:17:59.755
I was beginning to
think it was stolen.

284
00:17:59.779 --> 00:18:03.881
No. No. just lost. Definitely
not stolen by anyone.

285
00:18:03.950 --> 00:18:08.052
(CHUCKLES) Well. thank you
for finding it. And for bringing it.

286
00:18:11.090 --> 00:18:14.192
You don't think I'm a
total stalker now. do you?

287
00:18:15.628 --> 00:18:18.846
Hmm. no. I just
think you're weird.

288
00:18:20.599 --> 00:18:22.566
Like you always are.

289
00:18:22.635 --> 00:18:24.435
<i>(TOWARDS THE SUN</i> PLAYING)

290
00:18:24.504 --> 00:18:31.025
<i>♪ And I'm slipping away</i>

291
00:18:33.263 --> 00:18:36.764
<i>♪ Unseen by anyone</i>

292
00:18:41.070 --> 00:18:47.708
<i>♪ The light is turning gray</i>

293
00:18:55.467 --> 00:18:58.119
<i>♪ The day is done ♪</i>

294
00:18:58.987 --> 00:19:00.221
(LAUGHS)

295
00:19:04.443 --> 00:19:06.226
Whatcha doing?

296
00:19:06.295 --> 00:19:08.546
Work. Anything I can help with?

297
00:19:08.615 --> 00:19:13.851
You know. if you poured me an ounce
of whiskey. that would be awfully nice.

298
00:19:21.895 --> 00:19:23.895
Any leads? Hey!

299
00:19:24.196 --> 00:19:25.596
Ah!

300
00:19:25.665 --> 00:19:27.905
You know I can't
discuss that with you.

301
00:19:29.719 --> 00:19:31.352
Not too much.

302
00:19:42.648 --> 00:19:43.648
Okay.

303
00:19:44.833 --> 00:19:47.000
There ya go. Dad.

304
00:19:47.069 --> 00:19:49.336
Thanks. Bottoms up.

305
00:19:55.461 --> 00:19:58.495
You know. Derek Hale
would be a whole hale of a lot...

306
00:19:59.933 --> 00:20:01.532
A Hale of a lot?

307
00:20:03.903 --> 00:20:05.135
Hell of a lot?

308
00:20:06.038 --> 00:20:07.171
Hell.

309
00:20:07.940 --> 00:20:10.107
Yes.

310
00:20:10.175 --> 00:20:16.414
He would be a hell of a lot easier to catch
if we could get an actual picture of him.

311
00:20:16.482 --> 00:20:18.649
How do you not
have a picture of him?

312
00:20:18.718 --> 00:20:21.029
It's the weirdest thing. It's like
every time we try to get a mug shot.

313
00:20:21.053 --> 00:20:25.622
it's like two laser beams
were pointing at the camera.

314
00:20:26.492 --> 00:20:28.292
Nice.

315
00:20:28.344 --> 00:20:33.046
Oh. my God. Oh! God.
that ounce hit me like a brick.

316
00:20:33.115 --> 00:20:36.345
And I have said way too much.
and if you repeat any of that...

317
00:20:36.369 --> 00:20:38.830
Dad... it's me. I'm not
gonna say anything.

318
00:20:38.854 --> 00:20:40.153
Come on.

319
00:20:44.009 --> 00:20:46.494
See. the thing is
they're all connected.

320
00:20:46.562 --> 00:20:48.674
I mean. the bus
driver that got killed.

321
00:20:48.698 --> 00:20:50.442
he was an insurance investigator

322
00:20:50.466 --> 00:20:52.586
assigned to the Hale house fire.

323
00:20:53.769 --> 00:20:55.753
"Terminated under
suspicion of fraud."

324
00:20:55.821 --> 00:20:57.504
Exactly.

325
00:20:57.573 --> 00:20:58.989
Who else?

326
00:20:59.041 --> 00:21:01.609
The video store clerk
who got his throat slashed...

327
00:21:01.677 --> 00:21:04.045
He's a convicted
felon. history of arson.

328
00:21:04.113 --> 00:21:07.125
What about the other two guys.
the guys who got killed in the woods?

329
00:21:07.149 --> 00:21:09.545
Priors all over their
records including...

330
00:21:09.569 --> 00:21:10.735
Arson.

331
00:21:13.673 --> 00:21:16.633
So maybe they all had
something to do with the fire.

332
00:21:18.044 --> 00:21:20.694
Another shot? No.
no. no. no more.

333
00:21:20.763 --> 00:21:23.625
Dad. come on. You work
really hard. right? You deserve it.

334
00:21:23.649 --> 00:21:25.282
(SIGHS)

335
00:21:25.351 --> 00:21:27.930
Oh. my God. I'm gonna
have such a hangover.

336
00:21:27.954 --> 00:21:30.620
You mean you're gonna
have such a good night's sleep.

337
00:21:30.689 --> 00:21:33.290
(CHUCKLES)

338
00:21:33.359 --> 00:21:36.160
I'm gonna have an eternity
in the lowest circle of hell.

339
00:21:43.686 --> 00:21:46.520
MAN ON PHONE: <i>Scott. I noticed
you didn't hand in your paper today.</i>

340
00:21:46.589 --> 00:21:48.172
<i>If you need an extension.</i>

341
00:21:48.240 --> 00:21:49.668
<i>the best I can do is another
48 hours.</i> Goddamn it.

342
00:21:49.692 --> 00:21:50.907
Oh. son of a...

343
00:21:50.976 --> 00:21:52.409
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

344
00:21:52.478 --> 00:21:53.478
Not now. Mom.

345
00:21:54.764 --> 00:21:56.063
(KNOCKING)

346
00:21:56.132 --> 00:21:57.181
I said not now.

347
00:22:00.335 --> 00:22:02.870
Sorry. Your mom let me in.

348
00:22:05.808 --> 00:22:07.892
(EXHALES) Can we talk?

349
00:22:17.903 --> 00:22:21.555
Oh. Stiles. there's
just so many questions.

350
00:22:21.624 --> 00:22:23.173
Like what?

351
00:22:23.242 --> 00:22:28.178
Like if Derek wanted to kill
everyone involved with the fire.

352
00:22:29.581 --> 00:22:31.048
then why start with his sister?

353
00:22:31.116 --> 00:22:33.700
I mean. she had
nothing to do with it.

354
00:22:33.769 --> 00:22:36.337
And why make it look like
some kind of animal did it?

355
00:22:38.040 --> 00:22:41.158
When that cougar ended
up in the parking lot.

356
00:22:42.862 --> 00:22:44.495
I checked with animal control.

357
00:22:44.564 --> 00:22:49.266
You know the instances
of wild animal reports

358
00:22:49.335 --> 00:22:53.371
were up 70% over
the past few months?

359
00:22:53.439 --> 00:22:55.823
It's like they're
just going crazy.

360
00:22:55.891 --> 00:22:59.176
running out of the
woods. I don't know.

361
00:22:59.245 --> 00:23:01.605
Or something's scaring them out.

362
00:23:01.881 --> 00:23:02.980
Ah.

363
00:23:04.216 --> 00:23:05.315
Hmm.

364
00:23:11.257 --> 00:23:13.307
You know. I miss talking to you.

365
00:23:13.375 --> 00:23:15.009
It's like we never have time...

366
00:23:15.077 --> 00:23:16.989
Dad. you know. I have to
make a phone call. I'm sorry.

367
00:23:17.013 --> 00:23:18.378
I'll be right back.

368
00:23:19.815 --> 00:23:21.748
I do. I miss it.

369
00:23:23.902 --> 00:23:24.902
And I miss your mom.

370
00:23:24.970 --> 00:23:26.203
<i>(THROUGH THE DARK</i> PLAYING)

371
00:23:26.272 --> 00:23:28.522
<i>♪ Someone reaching for me now</i>

372
00:23:31.093 --> 00:23:32.542
What'd you say?

373
00:23:35.748 --> 00:23:41.468
<i>♪ Through the dark</i>

374
00:23:41.537 --> 00:23:43.804
<i>♪ Reaching for me now</i>

375
00:23:43.872 --> 00:23:45.239
Thanks.

376
00:23:50.963 --> 00:23:56.600
<i>♪ You need someone</i>

377
00:23:56.669 --> 00:23:59.169
<i>♪ To hear you when you sigh ♪</i>

378
00:23:59.238 --> 00:24:01.104
Do you want me to
say something first?

379
00:24:01.907 --> 00:24:03.840
No. Okay.

380
00:24:05.461 --> 00:24:07.581
Do you want me to leave
you alone for a few minutes?

381
00:24:08.564 --> 00:24:10.280
Why would I want that?

382
00:24:10.349 --> 00:24:13.884
I don't know. It's just that...

383
00:24:13.953 --> 00:24:16.120
You came in here and
said that you wanted to talk.

384
00:24:16.188 --> 00:24:18.789
and we've been sitting
here for like 10 minutes

385
00:24:18.858 --> 00:24:20.135
and you haven't
said anything yet.

386
00:24:20.159 --> 00:24:21.402
and it's starting
to freak me out.

387
00:24:21.426 --> 00:24:23.777
Sorry. It's a
little hard to start.

388
00:24:29.118 --> 00:24:32.186
This is going to
sound really ridiculous.

389
00:24:32.254 --> 00:24:37.891
And I guess I just... I don't
want you to laugh at me.

390
00:24:37.960 --> 00:24:39.576
I would never laugh at you.

391
00:24:48.187 --> 00:24:49.253
(EXHALES)

392
00:24:49.321 --> 00:24:51.087
It's about my family.

393
00:24:51.157 --> 00:24:52.256
Okay.

394
00:24:54.293 --> 00:24:56.893
A little while ago. I
caught them in a lie.

395
00:24:58.731 --> 00:25:01.365
A small one.

396
00:25:01.434 --> 00:25:05.085
When my aunt first arrived.
she had car trouble. and...

397
00:25:06.005 --> 00:25:08.772
My dad said it was a flat tire.

398
00:25:08.841 --> 00:25:12.401
but she said she
needed a jump start.

399
00:25:12.878 --> 00:25:16.479
Maybe it was just a
little miscommunication.

400
00:25:16.548 --> 00:25:18.760
Yeah. That's
what I thought. too.

401
00:25:18.784 --> 00:25:22.786
And then I found glass on her car
like her window had been smashed in.

402
00:25:25.323 --> 00:25:28.683
I've been overhearing some
really strange conversations.

403
00:25:31.597 --> 00:25:33.997
I think some of it
has to do with Derek.

404
00:25:34.066 --> 00:25:35.946
Are you sure? Yeah.

405
00:25:36.751 --> 00:25:37.930
I think that he's not...

406
00:25:37.954 --> 00:25:40.474
Hey. Scott. I'm coming
home late tonight.

407
00:25:41.707 --> 00:25:43.607
What? What... What's wrong?

408
00:25:43.676 --> 00:25:46.460
Is it... Is it my hair. makeup?

409
00:25:47.363 --> 00:25:49.596
No. No. nothing.

410
00:25:51.200 --> 00:25:53.250
You look beautiful.
You look amazing.

411
00:25:54.853 --> 00:25:56.387
SCOTT: Amazing.

412
00:25:56.455 --> 00:25:57.654
Why do you look amazing?

413
00:25:58.507 --> 00:26:00.007
Because. amazingly.

414
00:26:00.075 --> 00:26:03.376
I'm having dinner for once with
a member of the male gender

415
00:26:03.445 --> 00:26:05.125
who's over the age of 16.

416
00:26:05.181 --> 00:26:07.114
(CHUCKLES) Who?

417
00:26:07.182 --> 00:26:10.417
It's a medical rep that
came into the hospital today.

418
00:26:10.486 --> 00:26:12.030
Yeah. we just kind
of started talking.

419
00:26:12.054 --> 00:26:13.898
and the next thing I know
I'm saying yes to dinner

420
00:26:13.922 --> 00:26:16.834
and I'm really hating myself
for skipping the gym last week.

421
00:26:16.858 --> 00:26:18.091
What medical rep?

422
00:26:18.160 --> 00:26:19.660
(DOORBELL RINGS)

423
00:26:19.728 --> 00:26:22.762
That medical rep. And
I'm not... I'm not ready.

424
00:26:22.831 --> 00:26:24.242
I'm not ready. I'm not
done. I'm not ready.

425
00:26:24.266 --> 00:26:25.977
so if you could
please just get the...

426
00:26:26.001 --> 00:26:28.161
Get the door and talk
with him. okay. just...

427
00:26:29.521 --> 00:26:30.603
Be nice.

428
00:26:32.241 --> 00:26:34.007
(SIGHS) Just one minute. okay?

429
00:26:36.528 --> 00:26:38.194
(DOORBELL RINGING)

430
00:26:42.602 --> 00:26:43.884
(HEART BEATING)

431
00:26:52.328 --> 00:26:53.861
(DOORBELL RINGING)

432
00:26:53.929 --> 00:26:55.829
MELISSA: Scott! Get the door.

433
00:27:01.420 --> 00:27:03.420
(DOORBELL RINGING)

434
00:27:03.489 --> 00:27:06.723
Scott! For the love
of God. please!

435
00:27:07.410 --> 00:27:09.175
(HEARTBEAT THUMPING)

436
00:27:22.358 --> 00:27:23.807
MELISSA: Hey.

437
00:27:23.876 --> 00:27:24.908
What are you doing?

438
00:27:24.977 --> 00:27:26.443
Aren't you gonna invite him in?

439
00:27:29.882 --> 00:27:31.448
Hello there.

440
00:27:41.309 --> 00:27:43.121
Really? Slam the
door in my face?

441
00:27:43.145 --> 00:27:44.394
Come on. Scott.

442
00:27:44.463 --> 00:27:46.823
Take a second to
think that through.

443
00:27:47.015 --> 00:27:48.515
I'll tell her.

444
00:27:48.584 --> 00:27:50.395
That I used to be
a catatonic invalid

445
00:27:50.419 --> 00:27:52.686
with burns covering
half my face?

446
00:27:52.754 --> 00:27:54.471
Good luck with that.

447
00:27:54.540 --> 00:27:56.340
If you hurt her. if
you even touch her...

448
00:27:56.408 --> 00:27:58.186
Scott. if I may
interrupt your listing

449
00:27:58.210 --> 00:28:01.189
of the top five most
impotent-sounding threats for a moment.

450
00:28:01.213 --> 00:28:06.666
try and remember that I've
been in a coma for six years.

451
00:28:06.735 --> 00:28:09.480
Don't you think I'd like to have
dinner with a beautiful woman?

452
00:28:09.504 --> 00:28:11.020
MELISSA: Just...
Just half a second.

453
00:28:11.089 --> 00:28:12.389
Sorry.

454
00:28:14.226 --> 00:28:15.509
Or maybe...

455
00:28:15.577 --> 00:28:17.355
You think that I've
come up with an idea.

456
00:28:17.379 --> 00:28:22.148
Like how it might be easier to
convince you to be part of the pack

457
00:28:22.984 --> 00:28:24.417
if your mother is. too.

458
00:28:41.086 --> 00:28:45.889
You need to understand how
much more powerful we are together.

459
00:28:45.958 --> 00:28:48.278
you and me and Derek.

460
00:28:50.245 --> 00:28:52.178
Did you know

461
00:28:52.247 --> 00:28:54.526
that some of the most
successful military operations

462
00:28:54.550 --> 00:28:56.327
during the Second World War

463
00:28:56.351 --> 00:28:59.186
were the German U-boat attacks?

464
00:28:59.254 --> 00:29:01.583
Do you know what
they called them?

465
00:29:01.607 --> 00:29:05.375
Wolf packs. Did you know that?

466
00:29:06.946 --> 00:29:09.413
Or are you failing
history as well?

467
00:29:09.481 --> 00:29:11.381
I know the Germans lost the war.

468
00:29:12.084 --> 00:29:14.684
(CHUCKLES)

469
00:29:14.753 --> 00:29:17.966
I think you'll find that most
historians would argue that

470
00:29:17.990 --> 00:29:20.390
as a failure of leadership.

471
00:29:21.060 --> 00:29:23.388
And trust me. we don't
have that problem here.

472
00:29:23.412 --> 00:29:25.645
I'm ready. I'm
ready. Sorry again.

473
00:29:25.714 --> 00:29:26.980
(LAUGHS)

474
00:29:28.784 --> 00:29:29.784
Oh.

475
00:29:32.588 --> 00:29:33.603
Mom...

476
00:29:35.123 --> 00:29:36.490
Yes? Sweetheart.

477
00:29:40.446 --> 00:29:41.794
Have a good time.

478
00:29:44.033 --> 00:29:45.782
Okay.

479
00:29:45.851 --> 00:29:47.383
(ROCK MUSIC)

480
00:29:54.793 --> 00:29:56.409
(GRUNTING)

481
00:29:58.931 --> 00:30:00.397
(MUSIC STOPS)

482
00:30:01.066 --> 00:30:02.900
What the hell?

483
00:30:05.037 --> 00:30:06.402
Hey.

484
00:30:06.471 --> 00:30:08.391
I like your taste in music.

485
00:30:09.458 --> 00:30:13.009
I haven't heard this
one in a long time.

486
00:30:14.245 --> 00:30:16.396
(FAST-PACED POP TUNE)

487
00:30:16.465 --> 00:30:18.215
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

488
00:30:20.669 --> 00:30:22.102
I'm not scared of you.

489
00:30:24.606 --> 00:30:25.906
Come on.

490
00:30:27.660 --> 00:30:28.858
I'm not afraid.

491
00:30:31.380 --> 00:30:34.414
Yeah. You are.

492
00:30:36.351 --> 00:30:40.787
You know. I bet you haven't
had a day in your whole life

493
00:30:40.855 --> 00:30:43.255
where you haven't
been afraid of something.

494
00:30:45.493 --> 00:30:48.861
But you won't
have to be anymore.

495
00:30:48.931 --> 00:30:52.316
Not when you're one of us.

496
00:30:52.384 --> 00:30:55.652
If you just stay. I
swear... I'll be right back.

497
00:30:55.721 --> 00:30:58.522
I just... I just have to. um...

498
00:30:58.591 --> 00:31:02.559
I wouldn't be doing this if it
wasn't totally. incredibly important.

499
00:31:03.429 --> 00:31:05.589
It's all right. No. no. no.

500
00:31:05.764 --> 00:31:07.564
I wanna talk to you.

501
00:31:07.632 --> 00:31:10.767
There's actually nothing I
want to do more right now.

502
00:31:10.836 --> 00:31:13.636
Can you please stay?
Please? I'll be right back.

503
00:31:15.574 --> 00:31:16.574
Thank you.

504
00:31:39.998 --> 00:31:41.464
Everything okay?

505
00:31:41.533 --> 00:31:42.899
Mmm. I don't know.

506
00:31:42.968 --> 00:31:45.835
I just feel like we maybe
missed the turn for the restaurant?

507
00:31:47.072 --> 00:31:48.572
Hmm.

508
00:31:48.640 --> 00:31:50.818
Well. I'll pull over. We
can map it on your phone.

509
00:31:50.842 --> 00:31:51.842
Okay.

510
00:32:02.487 --> 00:32:03.720
(LAUGHS)

511
00:32:04.856 --> 00:32:06.372
What?

512
00:32:07.976 --> 00:32:11.336
I was just noticing that you
have the most incredible skin.

513
00:32:11.480 --> 00:32:13.179
It's flawless.

514
00:32:16.018 --> 00:32:17.018
That's a new one on me.

515
00:32:20.172 --> 00:32:21.412
Do you mind?

516
00:32:25.510 --> 00:32:26.542
(THUD)

517
00:32:26.612 --> 00:32:28.411
Oh. Sorry.

518
00:32:34.920 --> 00:32:36.536
(CRASH) Oh!

519
00:32:40.141 --> 00:32:44.244
Oh. are you kidding me? Stiles!

520
00:32:47.483 --> 00:32:49.483
Mrs. McCall? Yes!

521
00:32:49.551 --> 00:32:53.186
Wow. this is... This is just
crazy. What a coincidence. huh?

522
00:32:53.255 --> 00:32:55.021
(MELISSA LAUGHS MOCKINGLY)

523
00:32:55.090 --> 00:32:56.456
Nicely done. Scott.

524
00:33:00.128 --> 00:33:01.528
<i>Nicely done.</i>

525
00:33:09.288 --> 00:33:10.865
I mean... I do not
know what happened.

526
00:33:10.889 --> 00:33:12.600
You guys just came
out of nowhere.

527
00:33:12.624 --> 00:33:15.559
Came out of nowhere! We were
parked on the side of the road. Stiles.

528
00:33:15.627 --> 00:33:17.194
How crazy is that?

529
00:33:17.262 --> 00:33:18.640
I mean. we should probably
call the cops. you know.

530
00:33:18.664 --> 00:33:20.007
do like an accident
report thing.

531
00:33:20.031 --> 00:33:21.442
I don't think that's necessary.

532
00:33:21.466 --> 00:33:22.799
Are you sure?

533
00:33:22.867 --> 00:33:24.078
I think I'm feeling
a little whiplash.

534
00:33:24.102 --> 00:33:25.902
Whiplash? You hit us!

535
00:33:25.970 --> 00:33:28.716
I don't know. there's something
definitely wrong with my neck.

536
00:33:28.740 --> 00:33:31.941
I know you're there.
Scott. and I'm impressed.

537
00:33:32.010 --> 00:33:35.330
It's too bad most
teenagers aren't that smart.

538
00:33:35.430 --> 00:33:39.633
<i>It's like that one on the
lacrosse team... Jackson.</i>

539
00:33:39.701 --> 00:33:42.301
<i>Thinks he knows all about us.</i>

540
00:33:42.370 --> 00:33:45.238
<i>You know how they
say knowledge is power.</i>

541
00:33:45.306 --> 00:33:46.546
<i>Not in his case.</i>

542
00:33:49.011 --> 00:33:51.410
Jackson. Oh. no.

543
00:34:05.544 --> 00:34:07.226
This is it?

544
00:34:08.747 --> 00:34:09.747
This is the place?

545
00:34:11.917 --> 00:34:13.366
Go ahead.

546
00:34:21.677 --> 00:34:24.997
Is it safe? I don't want
rafters falling on my head.

547
00:34:25.397 --> 00:34:26.596
Go in.

548
00:34:40.879 --> 00:34:42.345
(WOOD CREAKS)

549
00:35:07.956 --> 00:35:09.121
What's in here?

550
00:35:10.124 --> 00:35:11.424
Everything you want.

551
00:35:30.011 --> 00:35:31.511
(HINGES CREAK)

552
00:35:37.586 --> 00:35:40.687
It's gonna be all
right. Trust me.

553
00:35:49.464 --> 00:35:53.065
JACKSON: This house...
It's the same house.

554
00:35:54.202 --> 00:35:55.802
What'd you say?

555
00:35:55.871 --> 00:35:57.954
I've dreamt about this place.

556
00:35:59.757 --> 00:36:02.692
I remember the staircase. I
remember these... These walls.

557
00:36:02.760 --> 00:36:04.861
I remember everything.

558
00:36:06.114 --> 00:36:07.313
You've been here?

559
00:36:11.787 --> 00:36:13.227
No. never. I dreamt it.

560
00:36:17.542 --> 00:36:18.841
There's no one else here.

561
00:36:22.097 --> 00:36:23.530
And no one else coming?

562
00:36:27.769 --> 00:36:29.035
(WHIMPERING)

563
00:36:29.104 --> 00:36:31.504
No... No. please...

564
00:36:31.572 --> 00:36:32.850
Please don't.
okay? I'll shut up.

565
00:36:32.874 --> 00:36:34.168
I'll never say
another word again.

566
00:36:34.192 --> 00:36:35.208
I'll leave Scott alone.

567
00:36:35.277 --> 00:36:38.361
Please. you can't
do this! Please!

568
00:36:39.914 --> 00:36:40.997
(SOBBING) I...

569
00:36:41.783 --> 00:36:43.366
I don't deserve it.

570
00:36:43.435 --> 00:36:44.584
I think you do.

571
00:36:44.652 --> 00:36:46.219
No! Look around you!

572
00:36:47.739 --> 00:36:50.702
Wouldn't there be someone
here trying to save you?

573
00:36:50.726 --> 00:36:52.492
There's no one here.

574
00:36:54.096 --> 00:36:58.264
And there's a reason. No one
cares that you drive an expensive car.

575
00:36:58.333 --> 00:37:00.528
No one cares that
you have perfect hair.

576
00:37:00.552 --> 00:37:05.054
and no one cares that you're
captain of the lacrosse team!

577
00:37:05.123 --> 00:37:06.123
Excuse me.

578
00:37:09.160 --> 00:37:10.627
Co-captain.

579
00:37:15.400 --> 00:37:16.799
(GROWLING)

580
00:37:21.005 --> 00:37:22.499
Move! No.

581
00:37:22.523 --> 00:37:25.024
Fine. I'll kill you. too.

582
00:37:25.110 --> 00:37:26.437
(WHISTLING SOUND)
Cover your eyes!

583
00:37:26.461 --> 00:37:27.510
(PINGING)

584
00:37:29.247 --> 00:37:30.780
(GLASS SHATTERING)

585
00:37:32.818 --> 00:37:34.333
(RAPID GUNFIRE)

586
00:37:42.110 --> 00:37:43.190
Scott! Go!

587
00:37:46.197 --> 00:37:47.931
(GUNFIRE CONTINUES)

588
00:37:51.202 --> 00:37:52.418
Run!

589
00:38:01.179 --> 00:38:02.179
(ROARS)

590
00:38:11.206 --> 00:38:12.238
(ELECTRONIC CHIME)

591
00:38:22.267 --> 00:38:23.866
(GASPING)

592
00:38:24.369 --> 00:38:25.835
(WHEEZING)

593
00:38:35.780 --> 00:38:37.046
(GULPING)

594
00:38:41.653 --> 00:38:43.320
Allison.

595
00:38:58.903 --> 00:39:00.203
Stop.

596
00:39:00.272 --> 00:39:03.606
MAN: It's all right. Scott.
You're gonna be all right.

597
00:39:17.322 --> 00:39:18.504
(GASPS)

598
00:39:18.573 --> 00:39:19.972
(COUGHING)

599
00:39:20.041 --> 00:39:21.674
I wouldn't get up just yet.

600
00:39:23.962 --> 00:39:25.862
Where am I... You're fine.

601
00:39:25.930 --> 00:39:29.648
And I've given you something that
should speed up the healing process.

602
00:39:35.857 --> 00:39:37.941
But you're a vet.

603
00:39:38.009 --> 00:39:40.576
That's very true.

604
00:39:40.645 --> 00:39:43.913
And 90% of the time. I'm
mostly treating cats and dogs.

605
00:39:45.416 --> 00:39:46.749
Mostly?

606
00:39:49.137 --> 00:39:50.669
Mostly.

607
00:40:02.968 --> 00:40:04.200
What is this place?

608
00:40:05.186 --> 00:40:06.952
Let's start with the basics.

609
00:40:07.022 --> 00:40:09.389
You know how every
family has its secrets?

610
00:40:10.825 --> 00:40:12.225
Ours are a little different.

611
00:40:18.399 --> 00:40:20.499
(DOOR THUDS)

612
00:40:20.568 --> 00:40:22.869
<i>(WHO ARE YOU. REALLY?</i> PLAYING)

613
00:40:22.938 --> 00:40:26.039
<i>♪ So you feel entitled
to a sense of control</i>

614
00:40:26.107 --> 00:40:28.574
<i>♪ And make decisions
that you think are your own</i>

615
00:40:28.643 --> 00:40:31.010
<i>♪ You are a stranger
here Why have you come?</i>

616
00:40:31.079 --> 00:40:32.328
<i>♪ Why have you come?</i>

617
00:40:32.396 --> 00:40:34.831
<i>♪ Lift me higher
Let me look at the sun</i>

618
00:40:34.899 --> 00:40:36.065
<i>♪ Look at the sun</i>

619
00:40:36.134 --> 00:40:38.534
<i>♪ And once I hear
them clearly say</i>

620
00:40:38.603 --> 00:40:43.172
<i>♪ Who? Who are you. really?</i>

621
00:40:43.241 --> 00:40:48.477
<i>♪ And where are you going?</i>

622
00:40:48.546 --> 00:40:51.080
<i>♪ Well. I've got
nothing left to prove</i>

623
00:40:51.149 --> 00:40:53.582
<i>♪ 'Cause I've got
nothing left to lose</i>

624
00:40:53.652 --> 00:40:56.052
<i>♪ See me bare my teeth for you</i>

625
00:40:56.121 --> 00:41:00.123
<i>♪ Who? Who are you? ♪</i>

626
00:41:02.777 --> 00:41:04.194
